The paper focuses on face recognition using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The proposed approach involves the fusion of features generated by different deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs), which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of templates, which is a common approach in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed approach in terms of recognition performance, which is a common topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR).
